day 13 of crew matrix : Average of  2 numbers 

IN C :
#include<stdio.h>
int main() {
float num1 , num2 , average ;
printf("Enter the first no : ");
scanf("%f",&num1 );
printf("Enter the second no :");
scanf("%f",&num2 );
average = (num1 + num2) / 2 ;
printf("The average of %.2f and %.2f is %.2f\n",num1,num2,average);
return 0;
}


O\P:
Enter the first number: 5.5
Enter the second number: 7.5
The average of 5.50 and 7.50 is 6.50


IN PYTHON :
num1 = float(input("Enter the first no : "))
num2 = float(input("Enter the second no : "))
average = (num1 +num2 ) / 2
print(f"The average of {num1} and {num2} is {average : .2f } ")

O\P:
Enter the first number: 5.5
Enter the second number: 7.5
The average of 5.5 and 7.5 is 6.50
 








